The paper presents a deep-learning-based framework for mapping human settlement extent from satellite images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of fully convolutional neural networks (FCN) for semantic segmentation also suggests relevance to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves geographic information systems (GIS) and spatial analysis, which could potentially relate to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
